A vintage-style illustration depicting an ornate Islamic geometric pattern forming the shape of a tree, with intricate arabesque branches spreading outward. Within the tree's canopy, small glowing vessels and containers hold swirling, luminous streams that flow between them, suggesting knowledge being passed from one generation to another. The tree's roots extend deep into layered earth showing archaeological-like strata of accumulated wisdom. The color palette features rich gold, deep teal, and warm amber tones reminiscent of traditional Malaysian batik and Islamic manuscript illumination. Elderly hands at the trunk gently guide the flowing streams upward toward younger hands reaching down from the branches. The entire scene has a warm, sepia-toned quality with subtle paper texture, evoking precious historical documents and the timeless act of preserving institutional memory.
